[According to a recent -- 21 Mar 2018 -- update, a 6th human death due to rabies, since the beginning of 2018, was recorded in Thailand on Sun 18 Mar 2018, in the province Buriram. Rabies killed 14 people last year [2017], up from 11 in 2016.

The situation of rabies in Bangkok since 2013 is as follows: 31 rabid dogs in 2013; 47 in 2014; 22 in 2015; 30 in 2016 and 47 in 2017 (see, in French, at https://www.thailande-fr.com/sante/61181-rage-en-thailande-un-sixieme-deces-dans-la-province-de-buriram. transl. SB).

According to Thailand's annual reports to the OIE, the numbers of rabies cases in animals, since 2015, are as follows: 2015 - 327; 2016 - 612; 2017 - 792. - Mod.AS]

